    "description": "1 hour far from Porto, there is a magical lagoon hidden in the mountains accessible from a short 20 minutes walk, Poço Verde 🌿 #lagoon #porto #portugal🇵🇹 #douro #hike \nDiscover Poço Verde: a hidden mountain lagoon 1 hour from Porto with a short 20-minute walk, clear water and scenic trails. Planning tips and what to expect. #lagoon #porto #portugal🇵🇹 #douro #hike\nLead\nPoço Verde is a hidden mountain lagoon in the north of Portugal, about one hour from Porto. Tucked into the hills of the Gerês region, the clear green water is reachable after a short 20-minute walk—making it an ideal day trip or quick nature escape.\n\nWhat Poço Verde is like\nThe lagoon sits in a sheltered mountain hollow, framed by rocks and lush vegetation. The water is notable for its green hue and calm surface, perfect for cooling off on warm days. Surrounding paths and small clearings provide spots to relax, change, or enjoy a picnic.\n\nGetting there\nFrom Porto: allow about one hour driving time toward the Gerês/Douro area. Exact directions depend on your starting point; follow local signs toward Poço Verde or Gerês natural pools. The final approach requires parking at a trailhead and a roughly 20-minute walk on a well-marked path that descends to the lagoon.\n\nThe short 20-minute walk\nThe trail is short but mountain terrain means uneven ground and some rocks—wear sturdy shoes or sandals with grip. The path is suitable for most walkers; bring water and a small snack. Expect a natural, unpaved trail with occasional tree cover.\n\nWhat to bring and tips\n- Swimwear and a towel for swimming or sunbathing.  \n- Water, sunscreen, and a hat—shade is limited in some spots.  \n- Sturdy footwear for the short hike.  \n- A small trash bag: keep the area clean and pack out any litter.  \n- Respect local rules and private property; use designated access points.\n\nBest time to visit\nWarm months are best for swimming; mornings or late afternoons offer quieter conditions. Weekdays tend to be less busy than weekends and holiday periods.\n\nNearby highlights\nPoço Verde sits in the broader Gerês/Douro area—known for mountain scenery, rivers, and hiking. Combine the visit with other nearby natural pools, short hikes, or a scenic drive through the Douro hills.\n\nClosing / Call to action\nPoço Verde is a well-kept secret north of Portugal—a compact adventure: one hour from Porto and a refreshing 20-minute walk to a green mountain lagoon. Planning to visit? Pack swimwear, solid footwear, and leave no trace to help preserve this natural spot. Have you been to Poço Verde or another hidden lagoon near Porto? Share your tips and photos to help others discover it.",
